    "content": "nullLoyalty Management\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Loyalty Management\n Get Started with Loyalty Management\n Control Who Sees What in Loyalty Management\n Loyalty Program Setup Basics\n Manage Loyalty Program Partners\n Manage and Work with Benefits\n Manage and Work with Vouchers\n Manage and Work with Promotions\n Global Promotions Management\n Learn About Global Promotions Management\n Set Up Global Promotions Management\n Design Promotions\n Run Promotions\n Manage Promotions\n Quick Promotions\n Create a Promotion\n Add Partner Products\n Set Up Promotions with Data Cloud\n Set Up Promotions With Campaigns\n Generate Targeted Member Lists for Promotions with Actionable Lists\n Apply Promotions and Update Members' Progress\n Promotion Calendar\n Clone Promotions\n View and Track Member Promotions\n Offer Promotions in Real Time with Marketing Cloud Personalization\n Flow Actions for Promotions\n Offer Games to Members\n Integrate Loyalty Management with External Systems\n Settings for Loyalty Processes\n Set Up Loyalty Processes\n Create Loyalty Program Processes by Using Promotion Setup\n Member Engagement Widgets\n Mobile SDK for Loyalty Management\n Manage Loyalty Program Members\n Loyalty Service Excellence\n Manage and View Transaction Journals\n Set Up Experiences for Loyalty Program Members\n Get a Head Start on Your Day with the Home Page\n Integrate Loyalty Management with Marketing Cloud\n Integrate Loyalty Management with Service Cloud\n Supported Loyalty Management Objects for Shield Platform Encryption\n Create a Loyalty Management Trial Org\n Loyalty Analytics Base App\n Deploy and Use Analytics for Loyalty\n Loyalty Management on Hyperforce\n Languages Supported by Loyalty Management\n Data Deletion for Loyalty Management\n Data Access and Export for Loyalty Management\n Restrict Data Processing for Loyalty Management\n Consent Management for Loyalty Management\n Data Archive for Loyalty Management\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nLOYALTY MANAGEMENT\nGlobal Promotions Management\n\nWith Global Promotions Management, marketing managers and loyalty program managers can design both pricing and non-pricing promotions. They can design the promotions to run as part of the company’s loyalty program or outside the loyalty program as part of the company’s 360-degree marketing strategy. Companies can use Global Promotions Management to run granular promotions with in-built limits and promotion launch emails. Also, your company’s customers get a real-time view of the promotions that are applicable for their cart and can apply the eligible promotions of their choice during checkout.\n\nLearn About Global Promotions Management\nLearn about the features of Global Promotions Management and the key roles involved. Explore the workflow to design and run promotions with Global Promotions Management.\nSet Up Global Promotions Management\nTurn on Global Promotions Management in your org and provide marketing managers the permission to design promotions by using the Global Promotions wizard. Connect Global Promotions Management with a Marketing Cloud business unit to automatically create promotion launch journeys in Marketing Cloud when marketing managers activate promotions.\nDesign Promotions\nWith Global Promotions Management, companies can run two types of promotions. Companies can run promotions as part of their loyalty program and run promotions for their complete customer base outside their loyalty program. Marketing managers can use the Promotion Console app to create promotions for the company’s loyalty program or outside the loyalty program. Marketing managers can also manage their day-to-day promotion management tasks from the Promotion Console app. Loyalty program managers and marketing managers can create loyalty promotions from the Loyalty Management app.\nRun Promotions\nAfter you activate your promotions, you can run the promotions for your customers. Eligible customers can use the promotion from the promotion’s start date time until the promotion’s end date time. If your promotion doesn’t have an end date time, then customers can use the promotion until you deactivate the promotion.\nManage Promotions\nAfter promotions are activated and running, marketing managers can track the usage of promotions among customers and loyalty program members. Marketing managers can also easily replicate seasonal promotions and promotions that run multiple times a year.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
